: \"ET from July 27-Aug. 10.\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is significant because NBC Universal is betting big on Peacock as a hub for Olympic coverage.\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Universal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 872, \"end\": 879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999997329121372, \"rank\": 2.6708541887305893e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal plans to stream all 2024Olympicsevents live on Peacock, including all 329 medal events, a first for the Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 911, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.9999999994993232, \"rank\": 5.006587138180212e-10, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999997329121372, \"rank\": 2.6708541887305893e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The awareness of Peacock, which now has 30 million subscribers, is significantly higher than it was for the Tokyo Olympics,  Hanson, in his first Olympic assignment, will serve as the morning host of \\\"Gold Zone\\\" while Iseman and Gbajabiamila, co-hosts of \\\"American Ninja Warrior\\\" on NBC, will co-host each day's closing \\\"Gold Zone\\\" coverage following Siciliano.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999997329121372, \"rank\": 2.6708541887305893e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Hanson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.11609710263593e-14, \"text\": \"Hanson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Hanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Hanson\"}, {\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.999578332577083, \"rank\": 0.0002159511742990921, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic viewership has tumbled mightily in the United States since Rio in 2016.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9987984651087568, \"rank\": 0.0009423685644786743, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those Brazil-based Games averaged a massive 27 million viewers in prime time, but since then, the key viewership arrow has been heading south.Per Sports Media Watch,the Tokyo Games were the first Summer Olympics to average fewer American viewers than the preceding Winter Games since Athens in 2004, which followed Salt Lake City in 2002.\", \"from\